# Temp Artifact Location

- Save temporary files, generated downloads, screenshots, UI dumps, ad-hoc logs, and manual test outputs under `temp/`.
- Do not place these artifacts in the repo root or source directories unless the file is intentionally meant to be versioned.
- Treat `temp/` as local-only workspace output and keep it out of git.
- If a generated file becomes long-term documentation, fixture, or script input, move it to the proper tracked location such as `docs/`, `scripts/`, or a dedicated fixture directory in the same change.
- When a task needs scratch output, prefer a named subdirectory such as `temp/android/`, `temp/screenshots/`, or `temp/debug/`.

## Example

```text
BAD: Save `wateray-window.xml`, screenshots, test zips, or ad-hoc downloads in the project root.
GOOD: Save them under `temp/` and only promote files into tracked directories when they are intentionally part of the repo.
```
